  "text": "Unlike supervised learning, where labeled instances are provided to the learner, in multiple instance learning scenarios [CITATION_1] , the learner is only provided with bags of instances labeled as either positive (where at least one instance is positive) or all negative. This is a close match to our problem setting, in which sentences are labeled with tags that should be assigned to one or more words.",
